## ğŸ›œ Wireless Access Points

Each VLAN includes a Wireless Access Point (WAP) for wireless connectivity.  
Each WAP will:
- Be assigned a static IP within its VLAN subnet (e.g., `.2`)
- Relay DHCP from the router to wireless devices.

